{"name":"Positronic Brain","type":"feature","img":"systems/opsandtactics/icons/svg/disc.svg","system":{"description":"<h3>Racial Traits</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Synthetics receive OSL as their native language for free, and can chose any language in the Synthetic Language Group as a secondary native language.</li>\n<li>Synthetics can not use magic, psionics, or incantations.</li>\n<li>Synthetics heal HP through the Craft (Structural) skill vehicle repairing action.</li>\n<li>Synthetics are immune to Pepper Spray, Bear Fogger, Tear gas, Pepperballs and Pava balls.</li>\n<li>Synthetics are immune to all Psionic (Telepathy) attacks, effects, and benefits.</li>\n<li>Synthetics are immune to all Spellschool (Conjuration), Healing Subschool and Spellschool (Necromancy) spells.</li>\n<li>Synthetics are immune to all Incantation (Hex) Incantations.</li>\n<li>Synthetics are considered Huge objects for the purpose of spells.</li>\n<li>Synthetics are considered Huge steel ingots for the purpose of Spellschool (Transmutation) spells.</li>\n<li>Synthetics are immune to the effects and benefits of all poisons, diseases, narcotics, drugs, potions, and pharmaceuticals.</li>\n<li>Synthetics do not have to consume food, water or air, and can not starve, become dehydrated, or suffocate.</li>\n<li>Synthetics can not be Sickened, Inebriated, Nauseated, Fatigued, or Exhausted.</li>\n<li>Synthetics do not take bleed damage.</li>\n<li>Synthetics are not affected by any augmentation effects that would reduce or increase their CHP.</li>\n<li>When Synthetics are caught in any EMP effect, they may roll a Fortitude Saving Throw [TN20] or be Stunned for 1d3 rounds. Any augmentations the synthetic has on their shell are immediately disabled, if they do not have any upgrades or other means to mitigate an EMP.</li>\n<li>Synthetics that are reduced to -1 CHP or below do not suffer from the Dying condition, and do not need to be stabilized. Any time a synthetic would be Dying, they are Disabled instead.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Racial Traits (Active Effect)</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Synthetics have a Mental Limit equal to 0.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Positronic Brain</h3>\n<p>The positronic brain is the mental aspect of a synthetic, housing all of their mental abilities and statistics. The positronic brain houses the Intelligence, Wisdom, and Charisma for the synthetic. Due to the nature of synthetics, their brain can be removed from the shell and placed in another. All positronic brains have a wireless receiver and broadcaster that can interact with any interfaceable object.</p>\n<p>Unlike AI units, synthetics have actual intelligence. They can learn, think, reason, have feelings, emotions, wants, desires, hopes and dreams.</p>\n<h3>Personality and Culture</h3>\n<p>Synthetic creatures, due to their mimicry of true life, have a large span of possible personalities. Synthetic culture is only vaguely recognizable to non-synths, revolving around electronics, software, programs and other digital nuances. Synthetics also often take and assimilate themselves into whatever culture that is around them.</p>\n<h3>Language</h3>\n<p>The native language of a Synthetic is dependent on what kind of language they were given at creation. All Synthetics know Open Source Language, and can choose Glass, Penguin, Fruit, Devil, or Beep as a secondary language for free.</p>\n<h3>Names</h3>\n<p>Synthetics usually have a long set of names. The first name is usually a chosen personal name, the middle name usually denotes their design, use, or model, though this is optional, and the last name is given, either by a creator, family, user, or randomly generated.</p>","summary":""},"effects":[{"label":"Brain Traits","icon":"systems/opsandtactics/icons/svg/disc.svg","origin":"Item.7Cfz5fsxjKV5xebp","duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"combat":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"disabled":false,"_id":"Km86Sqpsdi5RuZK6","changes":[{"key":"system.details.race","mode":2,"value":"Synthetic","priority":null},{"key":"system.ml.formula","mode":5,"value":"0","priority":null}],"tint":null,"transfer":true,"flags":{}}],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.7Cfz5fsxjKV5xebp"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"opsandtactics","systemVersion":"0.0.9","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1681244262397,"modifiedTime":1683080404415,"lastModifiedBy":"qDhNdGOjrAc4xpWx"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"qUf9EhhQBxZF46Rx":3},"_id":"3ESYWK8oxCchBauD"}
{"name":"Polaran (Recessive)","type":"feature","img":"systems/opsandtactics/icons/svg/dna2.svg","system":{"description":"<h3>Racial Traits</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Polarans have the Fast Healing ability based on their climate, or if they&rsquo;re wearing their chill collar. Fast Healing stops working when the race is reduced to &minus;10 CHP or fewer.\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Cold climates or wearing a chill collar in any climate:</strong> Polarans heal 1 bleed dice per round, and heal 1 HP per round</li>\n<li><strong>Very Cold climates:</strong> Polarans heal 2 bleed dice per round, and heal 2 HP per round</li>\n<li><strong>Extremely Cold climates:</strong> Polarans heal 3 bleed dice per round, and heal 3 HP per round</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>When a Polaran is not in an extremely cold, very cold, or cold climate, or is not wearing a chill collar, their base Combat Point Score drops to 10.</li>\n<li>Polarans have Polar as their native language.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Racial Traits (Active Effect)</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Polarans have a base Combat Point score of 16.</li>\n<li>Polarans CHP formula is <code>CON Score +1</code>.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Physical Description</h3>\n<p>A healthy polaran typically stands between 5-6&frac12;&rsquo;, and weighs between 130-180 lbs. The men and women are generally the same height. Polaran skin tone ranges from a pale flesh tone all the way to a snow white, and their hair ranges from a faint grey to bright white, with some possessing naturally blue hair, with silver and white being more common, almost exclusively straight and long. Eye color is also unique, ranging from a deep teal all the way to a deep dark blue, to assist in the snow. The average polaran lifespan is 110 years, reaching physical adulthood between the ages of 17-22.</p>\n<h3>Language</h3>\n<p>The native language of a Polaran is Polar, but Trade Bant is an often taught language, for trade.</p>\n<h3>Names</h3>\n<p>Polarans have two names, The first name being a given name, and is used to refer to the particular polar, the second name being their family name, that denotes their immediate family.</p>","summary":""},"effects":[{"label":"Racial Effects","icon":"systems/opsandtactics/icons/svg/dna2.svg","origin":"Item.VfoJEbTPJP2z6cqt","duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"combat":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"disabled":false,"_id":"VlIeiq9gmNfDZsE7","changes":[{"key":"system.details.race","mode":2,"value":"-Polaran"},{"key":"system.cp.max","mode":5,"value":"16"},{"key":"system.health.chp.formula","mode":5,"value":"(@con.score)+1"}],"tint":null,"transfer":true,"flags":{}}],"ownership":{"default":0,"qUf9EhhQBxZF46Rx":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.YgOKy30xNCFHVvnf"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"opsandtactics","systemVersion":"0.0.9","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1681848685014,"modifiedTime":1683080324949,"lastModifiedBy":"qDhNdGOjrAc4xpWx"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"4eGjMFxirGIjbxwS"}
{"name":"Kandari (Recessive)","type":"feature","img":"systems/opsandtactics/icons/svg/dna2.svg","system":{"description":"<h3>Racial Traits</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Kandari receive Kandari as their native language for free, and can chose 4 languages as a native languages in addition.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Racial Traits (Active Effect)</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Kandari have a base Combat Point score of 15.</li>\n<li>Kandari CHP formula is <code>CON Score +1</code>.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Physical Description</h3>\n<p>A healthy kandari typically stands between 5&frac12;-6&frac12;&rsquo;, and weighs between 150-200 pounds. Kandari skin tone ranges from a light flesh tone to a pale yellow, and their hair is almost exclusively black, and almost exclusively straight and long. Eye color is extremely unique, as they have the possibility to have any color of iris. Kandari also have two black dots above each of their eyebrows. The average kandari lifespan is 140 years, reaching physical adulthood between the ages of 24-28.</p>\n<h3>Language</h3>\n<p>The native language of a kandari is Kandari, but because of their ability to understand structure, patterns, and systems they pick up any language easily. English or Trade Bant is an often taught language, for trade. A kandari is capable of speaking any language of their home location, which will transcend the typical language spoken in their area or origin.</p>\n<h3>Names</h3>\n<p>Kandari usually have one long, complicated name, that spells out their personal name, family name, and current job title, in one neat package. Because of the cultural exchange, the first few syllables of their name is used by other races to denote them.</p>","summary":""},"effects":[{"label":"Racial Effects","icon":"systems/opsandtactics/icons/svg/dna2.svg","origin":"Item.VfoJEbTPJP2z6cqt","duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"combat":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"disabled":false,"_id":"VlIeiq9gmNfDZsE7","changes":[{"key":"system.details.race","mode":2,"value":"-Kandari"},{"key":"system.cp.max","mode":5,"value":"15"},{"key":"system.health.chp.formula","mode":5,"value":"(@con.score)+1"}],"tint":null,"transfer":true,"flags":{}}],"ownership":{"default":0,"qUf9EhhQBxZF46Rx":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.VfoJEbTPJP2z6cqt"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"opsandtactics","systemVersion":"0.0.9","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1681848685014,"modifiedTime":1683080301215,"lastModifiedBy":"qDhNdGOjrAc4xpWx"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"9T9TrdJ6siKPnpUa"}
{"name":"Armored Shell","type":"feature","img":"systems/opsandtactics/icons/svg/space-suit.svg","system":{"description":"<h3>Racial Traits</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Armored Shells have a natural 2/Ballistic, Bludgeoning, Slashing, Piercing and 1/Electric, Plasma damage reduction.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Racial Traits (Active Effect)</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Armored Shells have a base Combat Point score of 12.</li>\n<li>An Armored Shell's CHP formula is <code>CON Score + 1</code>.</li>\n<li>Armored Shells have a +4 Strength for the purposes of Carrying Capacity.</li>\n<li>Armored Shells gain 3 XHP per level. This is added after their total XHP for the level is calculated. Removing this shell also removes this XHP bonus.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Shell</h3>\n<p>The shell is the physical aspect of a synthetic, housing all of their physical abilities and statistics. The shell houses the Strength, Dexterity, and Constitution for the synthetic. The physical appearance of the shell varies greatly due to the personality and wealth of the synthetic, with some having a decidedly artificial appearance while others looking and even feeling natural in all aspects. Shells usually take a sentient-like appearance with a torso, two arms, and two legs. This is primarily done to be compatible with the various augmentations and equipment, and secondarily out of the unconscious narcissistic habit of their creators to design what is familiar. They can feasibly look like any race. Due to the mechanical, structural, and electrical nature of the shell, it does not heal or recover damage like natural creatures. A synth can change their shell for 100 WP, and it takes 1 day for the change to be completed. The only exception to this is the Frail shell. Frail shells are free and it takes 20 minutes to change into or out of. The limbs of a synthetic&rsquo;s shell can accept upgrades as though they were cyberlimbs, with a limit of 2 upgrades per limb. They may still replace these limbs with actual cyberlimbs as normal, with all of the benefits and penalties that they entail.</p>","summary":""},"effects":[{"label":"Shell Traits","icon":"systems/opsandtactics/icons/svg/space-suit.svg","origin":"Item.59J8Qv2X0nf2DeAz","duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"combat":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"disabled":false,"_id":"5RShxE6MddrWLpp5","changes":[{"key":"system.details.race","mode":2,"value":"-Armored"},{"key":"system.cp.max","mode":5,"value":"12"},{"key":"system.health.chp.formula","mode":5,"value":"(@con.score)+1"},{"key":"system.stats.carrying.formula","mode":5,"value":"((@str.score)+4)*4"},{"key":"system.health.xhp.formula","mode":5,"value":"((3+@con.mod)*(@lvl+1))+(3*@lvl)"}],"tint":null,"transfer":true,"flags":{}}],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.59J8Qv2X0nf2DeAz"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"opsandtactics","systemVersion":"0.0.9","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1681244983810,"modifiedTime":1683080381957,"lastModifiedBy":"qDhNdGOjrAc4xpWx"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"qUf9EhhQBxZF46Rx":3},"_id":"GsE2BL2SCddG7hls"}
{"name":"Kandari (Full)","type":"feature","img":"systems/opsandtactics/icons/svg/dna2.svg","system":{"description":"<h3>Racial Traits</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>When Kandari Release a Spell, Recite an Incantation, or use Psionics, the CP cost is 1 less.</li>\n<li>Kandari possess Darkvision, which allows them to see in total darkness, out to 50 feet. This vision is black-and-white only.</li>\n<li>Kandari receive Kandari as their native language for free, and can chose 4 languages as a native languages in addition.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Racial Traits (Active Effect)</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Kandari are Medium sized creatures.</li>\n<li>Kandari receive a &minus;4 Racial Recoil Penalty to recoil when using any weapon that has recoil.</li>\n<li>Kandari have a Mental Limit equal to <code>((6+WIS Score)&times;CL) + 70</code>.</li>\n<li>Kandari have a base Combat Point score of 15.</li>\n<li>Kandari CHP formula is <code>CON Score +1</code>.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Physical Description</h3>\n<p>A healthy kandari typically stands between 5&frac12;-6&frac12;&rsquo;, and weighs between 150-200 pounds. Kandari skin tone ranges from a light flesh tone to a pale yellow, and their hair is almost exclusively black, and almost exclusively straight and long. Eye color is extremely unique, as they have the possibility to have any color of iris. Kandari also have two black dots above each of their eyebrows. The average kandari lifespan is 140 years, reaching physical adulthood between the ages of 24-28.</p>\n<h3>Language</h3>\n<p>The native language of a kandari is Kandari, but because of their ability to understand structure, patterns, and systems they pick up any language easily. English or Trade Bant is an often taught language, for trade. A kandari is capable of speaking any language of their home location, which will transcend the typical language spoken in their area or origin.</p>\n<h3>Names</h3>\n<p>Kandari usually have one long, complicated name, that spells out their personal name, family name, and current job title, in one neat package. Because of the cultural exchange, the first few syllables of their name is used by other races to denote them.</p>","summary":""},"effects":[{"label":"Racial Effects","icon":"systems/opsandtactics/icons/svg/dna2.svg","origin":"Item.VfoJEbTPJP2z6cqt","duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"combat":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"disabled":false,"_id":"VlIeiq9gmNfDZsE7","changes":[{"key":"system.details.race","mode":5,"value":"Kandari"},{"key":"system.details.size","mode":5,"value":"Medium"},{"key":"system.cp.max","mode":5,"value":"15"},{"key":"system.health.chp.formula","mode":5,"value":"(@con.score)+1"},{"key":"system.ml.formula","mode":5,"value":"((6+@wis.score)*@lvl)+70"},{"key":"system.stats.recoil.kandari","mode":2,"value":"-4"}],"tint":null,"transfer":true,"flags":{}}],"ownership":{"default":0,"qUf9EhhQBxZF46Rx":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.VfoJEbTPJP2z6cqt"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"opsandtactics","systemVersion":"0.0.9","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1681848685014,"modifiedTime":1683080294760,"lastModifiedBy":"qDhNdGOjrAc4xpWx"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"RqaQM8dKHBu4YuYD"}
{"name":"Agile Shell","type":"feature","img":"systems/opsandtactics/icons/svg/space-suit.svg","system":{"description":"<h3>Racial Traits</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Agile Shells are vulnerable to electrical, fire, and cold attacks, and take twice as much damage from all electrical, fire and cold attacks and all effects with electrical damage are doubled in duration.</li>\n<li>All augmentations cost 50% less for an Agile Shell.</li>\n<li>Agile Shells have built in augmentative vision with 2 Ram and 5 HDD.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Racial Traits (Active Effect)</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Agile Shells have a base Combat Point score of 18.</li>\n<li>An Agile Shell's CHP formula is CON Score - 2.</li>\n<li>Agile Shells have a natural +1 dodge bonus to Defense.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Shell</h3>\n<p>The shell is the physical aspect of a synthetic, housing all of their physical abilities and statistics. The shell houses the Strength, Dexterity, and Constitution for the synthetic. The physical appearance of the shell varies greatly due to the personality and wealth of the synthetic, with some having a decidedly artificial appearance while others looking and even feeling natural in all aspects. Shells usually take a sentient-like appearance with a torso, two arms, and two legs. This is primarily done to be compatible with the various augmentations and equipment, and secondarily out of the unconscious narcissistic habit of their creators to design what is familiar. They can feasibly look like any race. Due to the mechanical, structural, and electrical nature of the shell, it does not heal or recover damage like natural creatures. A synth can change their shell for 100 WP, and it takes 1 day for the change to be completed. The only exception to this is the Frail shell. Frail shells are free and it takes 20 minutes to change into or out of. The limbs of a synthetic&rsquo;s shell can accept upgrades as though they were cyberlimbs, with a limit of 2 upgrades per limb. They may still replace these limbs with actual cyberlimbs as normal, with all of the benefits and penalties that they entail.</p>","summary":""},"effects":[{"label":"Shell Traits","icon":"systems/opsandtactics/icons/svg/space-suit.svg","origin":"Item.jQRYd1c2qI16TUOk","duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"combat":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"disabled":false,"_id":"TpZeqs0gwOy70i4T","changes":[{"key":"system.details.race","mode":2,"value":"-Agile"},{"key":"system.cp.max","mode":5,"value":"18"},{"key":"system.health.chp.formula","mode":5,"value":"(@con.score)-2"},{"key":"system.def.dodge.synth","mode":2,"value":"1"}],"tint":null,"transfer":true,"flags":{}}],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.jQRYd1c2qI16TUOk"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"opsandtactics","systemVersion":"0.0.9","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1681245218514,"modifiedTime":1683080375415,"lastModifiedBy":"qDhNdGOjrAc4xpWx"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"qUf9EhhQBxZF46Rx":3},"_id":"WGZ7J1jII7MB6aLA"}
