{"name":"Polaran (Full)","type":"feature","img":"systems/opsandtactics/icons/svg/dna2.svg","system":{"description":"<h3>Racial Traits</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Polarans are immune to cold environments. They do not have to make a Saving Throw against cold environments.</li>\n<li>Polarans are weak to hot environments. The Fortitude Saving Throw to resist hot environments is doubled.</li>\n<li>Polarans receive the extra feat Second Wind at 1st level for free, even if they do not meet the prerequisites.</li>\n<li>&nbsp;Polarans have a Natural Energy Resistance to cold. They gain 5/Cold DR.</li>\n<li>&nbsp;Polarans receive the extra feat Forgiving Damage (Any) at 1st level for free.</li>\n<li>Polarans have the Fast Healing ability based on their climate, or if they&rsquo;re wearing their chill collar. Fast Healing stops working when the race is reduced to &minus;10 CHP or fewer.\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Cold climates or wearing a chill collar in any climate:</strong> Polarans heal 1 bleed dice per round, and heal 1 HP per round</li>\n<li><strong>Very Cold climates:</strong> Polarans heal 2 bleed dice per round, and heal 2 HP per round</li>\n<li><strong>Extremely Cold climates:</strong> Polarans heal 3 bleed dice per round, and heal 3 HP per round</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>When a Polaran is not in an extremely cold, very cold, or cold climate, or is not wearing a chill collar, their base Combat Point Score drops to 10.</li>\n<li>Polarans have Polar as their native language.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Racial Traits (Active Effect)</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Polarans are Medium sized creatures.</li>\n<li>Polarans have a base Combat Point score of 16.</li>\n<li>Polarans CHP formula is <code>CON Score +1</code>.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Physical Description</h3>\n<p>A healthy polaran typically stands between 5-6&frac12;&rsquo;, and weighs between 130-180 lbs. The men and women are generally the same height. Polaran skin tone ranges from a pale flesh tone all the way to a snow white, and their hair ranges from a faint grey to bright white, with some possessing naturally blue hair, with silver and white being more common, almost exclusively straight and long. Eye color is also unique, ranging from a deep teal all the way to a deep dark blue, to assist in the snow. The average polaran lifespan is 110 years, reaching physical adulthood between the ages of 17-22.</p>\n<h3>Language</h3>\n<p>The native language of a Polaran is Polar, but Trade Bant is an often taught language, for trade.</p>\n<h3>Names</h3>\n<p>Polarans have two names, The first name being a given name, and is used to refer to the particular polar, the second name being their family name, that denotes their immediate family.</p>","summary":""},"effects":[{"label":"Racial Effects","icon":"systems/opsandtactics/icons/svg/dna2.svg","origin":"Item.VfoJEbTPJP2z6cqt","duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"combat":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"disabled":false,"_id":"VlIeiq9gmNfDZsE7","changes":[{"key":"system.details.race","mode":5,"value":"Polaran"},{"key":"system.details.size","mode":5,"value":"Medium"},{"key":"system.cp.max","mode":5,"value":"16"},{"key":"system.health.chp.formula","mode":5,"value":"(@con.score)+1"}],"tint":null,"transfer":true,"flags":{}}],"ownership":{"default":0,"qUf9EhhQBxZF46Rx":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.VfoJEbTPJP2z6cqt"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"opsandtactics","systemVersion":"0.0.9","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1681848685014,"modifiedTime":1683080317922,"lastModifiedBy":"qDhNdGOjrAc4xpWx"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"as2entL7KzM9biCx"}
{"name":"Polaran (Dominant)","type":"feature","img":"systems/opsandtactics/icons/svg/dna2.svg","system":{"description":"<h3>Racial Traits</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Polarans are immune to cold environments. They do not have to make a Saving Throw against cold environments.</li>\n<li>Polarans are weak to hot environments. The Fortitude Saving Throw to resist hot environments is doubled.</li>\n<li>Polarans receive the extra feat Second Wind at 1st level for free, even if they do not meet the prerequisites</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Racial Traits (Active Effect)</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Polarans are Medium sized creatures.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Physical Description</h3>\n<p>A healthy polaran typically stands between 5-6&frac12;&rsquo;, and weighs between 130-180 lbs. The men and women are generally the same height. Polaran skin tone ranges from a pale flesh tone all the way to a snow white, and their hair ranges from a faint grey to bright white, with some possessing naturally blue hair, with silver and white being more common, almost exclusively straight and long. Eye color is also unique, ranging from a deep teal all the way to a deep dark blue, to assist in the snow. The average polaran lifespan is 110 years, reaching physical adulthood between the ages of 17-22.</p>\n<h3>Language</h3>\n<p>The native language of a Polaran is Polar, but Trade Bant is an often taught language, for trade.</p>\n<h3>Names</h3>\n<p>Polarans have two names, The first name being a given name, and is used to refer to the particular polar, the second name being their family name, that denotes their immediate family.</p>","summary":""},"effects":[{"label":"Racial Effects","icon":"systems/opsandtactics/icons/svg/dna2.svg","origin":"Item.VfoJEbTPJP2z6cqt","duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"combat":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"disabled":false,"_id":"VlIeiq9gmNfDZsE7","changes":[{"key":"system.details.race","mode":2,"value":"Polaran"},{"key":"system.details.size","mode":5,"value":"Medium"}],"tint":null,"transfer":true,"flags":{}}],"ownership":{"default":0,"qUf9EhhQBxZF46Rx":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.kWaBkznh3zkNA39m"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"opsandtactics","systemVersion":"0.0.9","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1681848685014,"modifiedTime":1683080307957,"lastModifiedBy":"qDhNdGOjrAc4xpWx"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"bOU9hwTGY7eeeTXb"}
{"name":"Standard Shell","type":"feature","img":"systems/opsandtactics/icons/svg/space-suit.svg","system":{"description":"<h3>Racial Traits</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Standard Shells are vulnerable to electrical attacks, and take twice as much damage from all electrical attacks and all effects with electrical damage are doubled in duration.</li>\n<li>All augmentations cost 50% less for a Standard Shell.</li>\n<li>A Standard Shell gains a +3 bonus on all Knowledge skills.</li>\n<li>A Standard Shell gains a +6 on the Technology Use skill, and does not require any kind of equipment to perform any action under it.</li>\n<li>Standard Shells have built-in augmentative vision with 1 RAM and 2 HDD.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Racial Traits (Active Effect)</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Standard Shells have a base Combat Point score of 15.</li>\n<li>A Standard Shell's CHP formula is CON Score - 1.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Shell</h3>\n<p>The shell is the physical aspect of a synthetic, housing all of their physical abilities and statistics. The shell houses the Strength, Dexterity, and Constitution for the synthetic. The physical appearance of the shell varies greatly due to the personality and wealth of the synthetic, with some having a decidedly artificial appearance while others looking and even feeling natural in all aspects. Shells usually take a sentient-like appearance with a torso, two arms, and two legs. This is primarily done to be compatible with the various augmentations and equipment, and secondarily out of the unconscious narcissistic habit of their creators to design what is familiar. They can feasibly look like any race. Due to the mechanical, structural, and electrical nature of the shell, it does not heal or recover damage like natural creatures. A synth can change their shell for 100 WP, and it takes 1 day for the change to be completed. The only exception to this is the Frail shell. Frail shells are free and it takes 20 minutes to change into or out of. The limbs of a synthetic&rsquo;s shell can accept upgrades as though they were cyberlimbs, with a limit of 2 upgrades per limb. They may still replace these limbs with actual cyberlimbs as normal, with all of the benefits and penalties that they entail.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","summary":""},"effects":[{"label":"Shell Traits","icon":"systems/opsandtactics/icons/svg/space-suit.svg","origin":"Item.gnpZ4YZX2zeRKeLp","duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"combat":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"disabled":false,"_id":"lbYcUEENmCoUfnLC","changes":[{"key":"system.details.race","mode":2,"value":"-Standard"},{"key":"system.cp.max","mode":5,"value":"15"},{"key":"system.health.chp.formula","mode":5,"value":"(@con.score)-1"}],"tint":null,"transfer":true,"flags":{}}],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.gnpZ4YZX2zeRKeLp"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"opsandtactics","systemVersion":"0.0.9","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1681244823422,"modifiedTime":1683080395713,"lastModifiedBy":"qDhNdGOjrAc4xpWx"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"qUf9EhhQBxZF46Rx":3},"_id":"i7MqTsAfWQDEirKT"}
{"name":"Frail Shell","type":"feature","img":"systems/opsandtactics/icons/svg/space-suit.svg","system":{"description":"<h3>Racial Traits</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Frail Shells are vulnerable to electrical, fire, and cold attacks, and take twice as much damage from all electrical, fire, and cold attacks and all effects with electrical damage are doubled in duration.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Racial Traits (Active Effect)</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Frail Shells have a base Combat Point score of 10.</li>\n<li>A Frail Shell's CHP formula is <code>CON Score - 2</code>.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Shell</h3>\n<p>The shell is the physical aspect of a synthetic, housing all of their physical abilities and statistics. The shell houses the Strength, Dexterity, and Constitution for the synthetic. The physical appearance of the shell varies greatly due to the personality and wealth of the synthetic, with some having a decidedly artificial appearance while others looking and even feeling natural in all aspects. Shells usually take a sentient-like appearance with a torso, two arms, and two legs. This is primarily done to be compatible with the various augmentations and equipment, and secondarily out of the unconscious narcissistic habit of their creators to design what is familiar. They can feasibly look like any race. Due to the mechanical, structural, and electrical nature of the shell, it does not heal or recover damage like natural creatures. A synth can change their shell for 100 WP, and it takes 1 day for the change to be completed. The only exception to this is the Frail shell. Frail shells are free and it takes 20 minutes to change into or out of. The limbs of a synthetic&rsquo;s shell can accept upgrades as though they were cyberlimbs, with a limit of 2 upgrades per limb. They may still replace these limbs with actual cyberlimbs as normal, with all of the benefits and penalties that they entail.</p>","summary":""},"effects":[{"label":"Shell Traits","icon":"systems/opsandtactics/icons/svg/space-suit.svg","origin":"Item.LZ2fhmJ4SYa0t9Ad","duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"combat":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"disabled":false,"_id":"a67qNpeHstQA6nXn","changes":[{"key":"system.details.race","mode":2,"value":"-Frail"},{"key":"system.cp.max","mode":5,"value":"10"},{"key":"system.health.chp.formula","mode":5,"value":"(@con.score)-2"}],"tint":null,"transfer":true,"flags":{}}],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.LZ2fhmJ4SYa0t9Ad"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"opsandtactics","systemVersion":"0.0.9","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1681244711994,"modifiedTime":1683080387561,"lastModifiedBy":"qDhNdGOjrAc4xpWx"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"qUf9EhhQBxZF46Rx":3},"_id":"xbQGjdK1Zt8qevDL"}
